<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL PAN, VIBRATION DAMPER, OIL
        PUMP, WATER PUMP, AND FRONT COVER - Installation - Front Cover and Water Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Front Cover and Water Pump</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Failure to properly install the front cover may result in engine damage. To properly install the
                    front cover, the water pump must be installed before tightening the front cover mounting bolts. Four
                    of the water pump mounting bolts also secure the front cover.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200523" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1937.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Gaskets and Applying RTV to the Front Cover</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">New Gaskets</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Sealant Locations</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position two new gaskets on the front cover. Apply RTV sealant in the remaining grooves of
                the front cover and around the front cover dowel pins.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200524" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1419.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Front Cover to the Crankcase</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover Mounting Bolts</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten the front cover to the crankcase. Install the front cover mounting bolts finger
                tight.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200521" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1522.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Water Pump Gasket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water Pump Gasket</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water Pump</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place a new gasket in the water pump gasket groove.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Failure to properly mount the water pump and obtain a correct seal may result in engine damage. To
                    properly mount the water pump and obtain a correct seal, install the water pump mounting bolts into
                    their proper locations.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1200522" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg1/EG1526.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Aluminum Water Pump Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">30 mm (1-1/4 in)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">80 mm (3-1/4 in)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">100 mm (4 in)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200537" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg8/EG8526.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="328px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Cast Iron Water Pump Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">30 mm (1-1/4 in)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">60 mm (2-1/2 in)</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">100 mm (4 in)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f1200525" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg3/EG3333.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Front Cover and Water Pump</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Water Pump</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Cover</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the water pump on the front cover. Install the water pump mounting bolts and tighten
                the bolts to the standard torque values.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the front cover mounting bolts to the standard torque value.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply a thin coat of new coolant to the coolant filter gasket. Thread the coolant filter
                onto the filter header until the gasket touches the header. Tighten the coolant filter by hand an
                additional 1/2 turn.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open the coolant shutoff valve on the water pump, or the two shutoff valves located on the
                side of the engine (if equipped).
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
